               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18210606-107-person1213">
                  THOMAS 
                  HAMILTON
               <interp inst="t18210606-107-person1213" type="surname" value="HAMILTON"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18210606-107-person1213" type="given" value="THOMAS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18210606-107-person1213" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am an officer. On the 29th of May, between nine and ten o'clock at night, I stopped the prisoner, in Cable-street, about half a mile from Ames's, with this cask, wrapped in his apron; I asked what it was, he said, a cask of her rings, which he was taking to Mrs. Norton's, in White's-yard, and a strange man gave them to him, opposite a shop, below Shadwell office.</p>
               <p>(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
